OVERVIEW:
SectorWars 2102 core gameplay mechanics covering turn-based systems, combat resolution, trading economy, colonization requirements, and ship management systems.

FACTS:
* Turn-based game with 1000 turns allocated per day
* Unused turns do not carry over to next day
* Turn consumption: travel (1 turn), dock/undock (1 turn each), combat initiation (varies), planetary development (varies)
* Zero turn cost: defending attacks, upgrading ships, trading while docked
* Combat success based on: drone count, ship type, shields, hull, random elements
* Ship destruction ejects player to indestructible escape pod with all credits retained
* Escape pods have substantially higher turn cost for movement
* Commodities trade through ports with 12 class types (0-11)
* Prices fluctuate based on supply/demand and sector characteristics
* Planet colonization requires 10,000 population units + 10,000 credits
* Population purchased from region's Sector 1 population hub at 50 credits per unit
* Team maximum: 4 players for balance
* Ship insurance available at friendly ports for partial value recovery
* Credits stored virtually (never lost on ship destruction)
* Cargo lost on ship destruction

TERMINOLOGY:
* Turn: Fundamental action currency, 1000 per day allocation
* Sector: Fundamental unit of space, contains ports/planets/ships/drones
* Port: Trading station with class (0-11) determining buy/sell inventory
* Dock: Attach to port (1 turn cost), enables instant trading
* Escape Pod: Indestructible survival craft, high turn cost for movement
* Colonization: Claiming planet with 10k population + 10k credits
* Team: Cooperative alliance (max 4 players) with shared resources
* Drones: Autonomous combat units (1000 credits each)
* Citadel: Planetary defense structure with levels 1-10

TURN_COSTS:
* Sector travel: 1 turn (modified by ship speed)
* Dock: 1 turn
* Undock: 1 turn
* Trading while docked: 0 turns
* Combat initiation: Varies by target
* Defending: 0 turns (automatic)
* Ship upgrades: 0 turns
* Planetary development: Varies

SHIP_ACQUISITION:
* Starting ship: Light Freighter (received at first login)
* Purchase locations: Major shipyards
* Insurance: Available at friendly ports
* Destruction result: Eject to escape pod, retain credits, lose cargo
* Manual eject: Player can abandon ship (leaves intact for others to claim)

COMBAT_SYSTEM:
* Combat drones: 1000 credits each from military outposts
* Ship drone capacity: 0-12 depending on ship type
* Combat triggers: player attack, hostile NPC sectors, targeted by enemies
* Resolution factors: drone count, ship defensive stats, random tactical elements
* Turn cost: Attacker pays turns, defender pays zero

TRADING_ECONOMY:
* Commodities: Ore, Basic Food, Gourmet Food, Fuel, Technology, Exotic Technology, Luxury Goods
* Port classes determine buy/sell inventory
* Price spread: typical buy price = sell price * 0.8
* Market dynamics: prices rise in shortages, fall in surplus
* Player impact: high trading volume temporarily affects sector values
* Population: Special commodity only from Earth, 50 credits/unit

PORT_CLASSES:
* Class 0 (Sol Station): Buys/sells all commodities
* Class 1: Buys Ore, sells Basic Food/Fuel/Technology
* Class 2: Buys Basic Food, sells Ore/Fuel/Technology
* Class 3: Buys Fuel, sells Ore/Basic Food/Technology
* Class 4: Buys Technology, sells Ore/Basic Food/Fuel
* Class 5: Buys Luxury Goods, sells Ore/Basic Food/Fuel/Technology
* Class 6: Buys Ore+Basic Food, sells Fuel+Technology
* Class 7: Buys Fuel+Technology, sells Ore+Basic Food
* Class 8 (Black Hole): Buys all, sells nothing
* Class 9 (Nova): Sells all, buys nothing
* Class 10: Buys Gourmet Food, sells Technology+Luxury Goods
* Class 11: Buys Exotic Technology, sells advanced components

COLONIZATION_SYSTEM:
* Requirements: 10,000 population units + 10,000 credits
* Transport: Each population unit occupies 1 cargo space
* Development: Factory, Farm, Mine, Defense (levels 1-10), Research
* Income: Based on population and infrastructure
* Population growth: Natural expansion over time once established
* Specialization types: Agricultural, Industrial, Military, Research, Balanced

TEAM_MECHANICS:
* Maximum members: 4 players
* Shared resources: Team treasury with 12 resource types
* Collective defense: Coordinated territory protection
* Team planets: Shared production benefits
* Fleet operations: Multi-ship coordinated combat

PLAYER_PROGRESSION:
* Credit accumulation: Total wealth earned
* Planets owned: Territory control metric
* Citadel levels: Defensive infrastructure development (1-10)
* Ports owned: Commercial infrastructure control
* Ships owned: Fleet size and composition
* Military rank: Achievement-based (see Ranking.aispec)

CONSTRAINTS:
* Turns cannot exceed daily allocation (1000)
* Unused turns expire at day rollover
* Teams limited to 4 players maximum
* Planet colonization minimum: 10k population + 10k credits
* Population only from Sector 1 population hub of each region
* Credits never lost on ship destruction
* Cargo always lost on ship destruction
* Escape pod movement has high turn cost penalty
* Combat initiation costs turns, defense is free

